             - he is a <rs id="t18290910-205-viclabel1145" type="occupation">carman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290910-205-victim1910 t18290910-205-viclabel1145"></join>. The prisoner was in his employ on the 15th of July - he received money to pay charges for Kennel coal, at the Docks; I gave him 2l. 5s. 6d. first, and then he sent home for 3l. more, which I sent him - he did not return; he was found by the officer about a month afterwards - he had been about seven or eight months in our employ.</p>
